 ðŸ“‚ Directory Enumeration â€“ Gobuster

**Gobuster** is a fast command-line tool used for directory and file brute-forcing on web servers.  
It helps uncover hidden directories, files, APIs, and backup resources that may expose sensitive functionality or misconfigurations during web penetration testing.

Gobuster works by sending HTTP requests using a wordlist and identifying valid responses based on status codes, response length, and extensions.

ðŸ”¹ Common Gobuster Usage

# Basic directory enumeration
gobuster dir -u https://www.example.com -w common.txt

# Use custom wordlist and file extensions
gobuster dir -u https://www.example.com -w custom.txt -x php,html,txt

# Recursive enumeration (scan discovered subdirectories)
gobuster dir -u https://www.example.com -w wordlist.txt -r

# Start enumeration from a specific path
gobuster dir -u https://www.example.com/subdir/ -w common.txt

# Filter results by HTTP status codes
gobuster dir -u https://www.example.com -w wordlist.txt -x php,html -s 200,204,301,302

# Use multiple HTTP methods
gobuster dir -u https://www.example.com -w wordlist.txt -x php -X GET,POST

# Add URL path prefix
gobuster dir -u https://www.example.com -w wordlist.txt -P /app/

# Ignore response length to reduce false positives
gobuster dir -u https://www.example.com -w wordlist.txt -z
